HEADWORD: Macle
<hw>Ma"cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>macula</ets> a
spot: cf. F. <ets>macle</ets>. Cf. <er>Mackle</er>,
<er>Mascle</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Chiastolite;
-- so called from the tessellated appearance of a cross section. See
<er>Chiastolite</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A crystal having a similar
tessellated appearance.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A twin
crystal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Macleaya</ent>⟦br⟧
